</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Tricep Extension Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How To Do</strong>&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand facing a cable machine, set at head height.</li>



<li>Feet hip-width apart for stability.</li>



<li>Use a straight bar or rope attachment.</li>



<li>Keep your upper arms in contact with your trunk.</li>



<li>Push the cable down towards the hips, straightening elbows.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows close to your head and pointed forward to isolate the triceps effectively.</li>



<li>Extend your arms slowly and smoothly, then lower the weight back with equal control to maximize triceps engagement.</li>



<li>Engage your core and maintain a straight posture throughout the exercise to support your upper body and enhance stability.</li>
</ul>



