<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Arnold-Press">Dumbbell Arnold Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-arnold-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell Arnold press</a> is a compound exercise that primarily works the front and sides of your <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537056/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulder muscles</a> (deltoids). It also engages the triceps, the upper trapezius, and the muscles underneath your armpits (<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK531457/#:~:text=The%20serratus%20anterior%20is%20a,inferior%20angle%20of%20the%20scapula." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">serratus anterior</a>).&nbsp;</p>



<p>Working the shoulder at multiple angles promotes balanced development of the deltoids and supporting muscle groups. This exercise is also functional and contributes to overall health.</p>



<p>A 2017 study shows <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Amritashish-Bagchi/publication/322132613_Comparison_among_the_EMG_Activity_of_the_Anterior_Deltoid_and_Medial_Deltoid_During_Two_Variations_of_Dumbbell_Shoulder_Press_Exercise/links/5c7bad03299bf1268d33da6f/Comparison-among-the-EMG-Activity-of-the-Anterior-Deltoid-and-Medial-Deltoid-During-Two-Variations-of-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press-Exercise.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">greater muscle activation rates</a> during the Arnold press than a traditional overhead press. Specifically, Arnold presses activate the front deltoid 29% more and the side deltoid 14% more.</p>



